As a lumberjack, you are cutting down trees. But deforestation has severe consequences.

Forests absorb carbon dioxide and release oxygen. Without them, the planet's temperature rises faster.


-> What are the effects?
    <<jump EffectsResponse>>
->What can we do to stop this?
    <<jump PreventiveResponse>>



===

title:EffectsResponse
tags:
---

Cutting trees destroys habitats, accelerates climate change, and harms biodiversity.

===

title:PreventiveResponse
tags:
---

Reduce logging, plant more trees, and use sustainable practices.

